Hoodlums have attacked the Ukpor High School training camp being used by INEC to train its officials ahead of the general elections. It was gathered that the hoodlums invaded the school located in the Nnewi South Local Government Area of Anambra State and disrupted the activities of the electoral commission, trainers, and trainees. A source said, “We thank God there was no loss of life in the attack. There is a need for adequate security to be beefed up around the area so that these INEC officials will be allowed to work and ensure hitch-free elections next. Confirming the incident, the Anambra State Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Tochukwu Ikenga, said, “No life was lost. Joint security patrols have been intensified in the area and efforts are still ongoing to track down the criminal elements. Further development shall be communicated, please.”